The paper deals with the use of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) for solving linear inverse problems, such as compressed sensing, super-resolution, and inpainting. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) categories. The paper also discusses the use of projected gradient descent (PGD) and the design of measurement matrices, which are topics related to Information Theory (cs.IT), Numerical Analysis (cs.NA), and Multimedia (cs.MM). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.CV and cs.LG, followed by cs.IT, cs.NA, and cs.MM.
